  <sect3 role="package">
    <title>Introduction to gnome-chess</title>

    <para>
      <application>gnome-chess</application> is a 2D/3D chess game, 
      where games can be played between a combination of human and 
      computer players.
    </para>

    &lfs76_checked;

    <bridgehead renderas="sect4">Package Information</bridgehead>
    <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Download (HTTP): <ulink url="&gnome-chess-download-http;"/>
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Download (FTP): <ulink url="&gnome-chess-download-ftp;"/>
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Download MD5 sum: &gnome-chess-md5sum;
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Download size: &gnome-chess-size;
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Estimated disk space required: &gnome-chess-buildsize;
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Estimated build time: &gnome-chess-time;
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>

    <bridgehead renderas="sect4">Gnome Chess Dependencies</bridgehead>

    <bridgehead renderas="sect5">Required</bridgehead>
    <para role="required">
      <xref linkend="gtk3"/>,
      <xref linkend="gobject-introspection"/>,
      <xref linkend="desktop-file-utils"/>,
      <xref linkend="itstool"/>,
      <xref linkend="librsvg"/>, and
      <xref linkend="hicolor-icon-theme"/>
    </para>

    <bridgehead renderas="sect5">Optional</bridgehead>
    <para role="optional">
    <ulink url="http://ftp.gnu.org/gnu/chess/">gnuchess</ulink> (to play against computer)      
    </para>

    <para condition="html" role="usernotes">User Notes:
      <ulink url="&blfs-wiki;/gnome-chess"/>
    </para>
  </sect3>

  <sect3 role="installation">
    <title>Installation of Gnome Chess</title>

    <para>
      Install <application>gnome-chess</application> by running the following
      commands:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>./configure --prefix=/usr     \
--disable-static  \
--sysconfdir=/etc &amp;&amp;
make</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      This package does not come with a test suite.
    </para>

    <para>
      Now, as the <systemitem class="username">root</systemitem> user:
    </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>make install</userinput></screen>

  </sect3>

